ENTRY       EC 2.4.1.304                Enzyme
NAME        UDP-Gal:alpha-D-GlcNAc-diphosphoundecaprenol beta-1,4-galactosyltransferase;
            WfeD;
            UDP-Gal:GlcNAc-R 1,4-Gal-transferase;
            UDP-Gal:GlcNAc-pyrophosphate-lipid beta-1,4-galactosyltransferase
CLASS       Transferases;
            Glycosyltransferases;
            Hexosyltransferases
SYSNAME     UDP-alpha-D-galactose:N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosaminyl-diphospho-ditrans,octacis-undecaprenol beta-1,4-galactosyltransferase
REACTION    UDP-alpha-D-galactose + N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosaminyl-diphospho-ditrans,octacis-undecaprenol = UDP + beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-alpha-D-GlcNAc-diphospho-ditrans,octacis-undecaprenol [RN:R10433]
ALL_REAC    R10433
SUBSTRATE   UDP-alpha-D-galactose [CPD:C00052];
            N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosaminyl-diphospho-ditrans,octacis-undecaprenol [CPD:C01289]
PRODUCT     UDP [CPD:C00015];
            beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-alpha-D-GlcNAc-diphospho-ditrans,octacis-undecaprenol [CPD:C20618]
COMMENT     The enzyme is involved in the the biosynthesis of the O-polysaccharide repeating unit of the bacterium Shigella boydii B14. The activity is stimulated by Mn2+ or to a lesser extent by Mg2+, Ca2+, Ni2+ or Pb2+.
